**Query 1 (Class.forName - 3 findings)**: All 3 cases (MessageStoreFactory, TieredFileQueue, TieredStoreUtil) read class names from broker configuration files, not network input. Two have asSubclass() type constraints. Submitted as Manual Review due to potential admin API config modification risk.

**Query 2 (Fastjson - 15 findings)**: All calls use typed parseObject overloads (JSON.parseObject(data, ConcreteClass.class) or TypeReference). No autoType support enabled in codebase (no ParserConfig.setAutoTypeSupport() or Feature.SupportAutoType found). Without autoType, @type fields cannot instantiate arbitrary classes. Submitted as False Positives.

**Query 3 (ServiceProvider - 8 findings)**: Standard Java SPI pattern - class names read from META-INF classpath resource files bundled at deployment time. No user-controlled network input flows to class loading. Submitted as False Positives.

**Query 4 (Broker processor fastjson - 22 findings)**: All trace back to RemotingSerializable.decode() which uses JSON.parseObject(data, ConcreteClass.class). Without autoType, arbitrary class instantiation from @type fields is not possible. Submitted as False Positives (consolidated with Query 2 findings).
